      "copy": {
        "paragraphs": [
          "Harris County sits at the heart of the Houston metro and includes a mix of large cities, suburbs, and specialized districts—each with its own property tax picture.",
          "Published rates from the Texas Comptroller and local appraisal districts help compare typical combined burdens across places like Houston and Pasadena, but your bill still depends on how jurisdictions overlap where the property sits.",
          "Use this calculator to explore how estimated taxes change across municipalities or school districts when you hold home value constant.",
          "Enter your property value below and choose a city when you know it to get a clearer planning estimate of annual and monthly property taxes."
        ],
        "disclaimer": "This page provides estimates for planning and comparison. Actual tax bills depend on appraisal, exemptions, and overlapping taxing units (county, city, school, and special districts). Verify amounts with your county appraisal district and local taxing entities."
      },
