      "copy": {
        "paragraphs": [
          "Dallas County anchors the eastern side of the Dallas–Fort Worth region, with dense urban districts alongside fast-growing suburbs—each subject to different combinations of city, school, and county rates.",
          "Effective-rate style figures from Texas Comptroller workbooks are useful for head-to-head comparisons of Dallas versus Plano or other cities in the county, before you layer in homestead and exemption details.",
          "This tool is especially helpful when you are weighing a move within North Texas and want a quick comparison of typical tax load at the same home value.",
          "Enter your property value below and select a city when you can to narrow the estimate toward the place you have in mind."
        ],
        "disclaimer": "This page provides estimates for planning and comparison. Actual tax bills depend on appraisal, exemptions, and overlapping taxing units (county, city, school, and special districts). Verify amounts with your county appraisal district and local taxing entities."
